能的创作者，WhatsApp 最终将添加支付服务以将其货币化。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>该公司表示，隐私也是关键。频道的管理员信息不会共享，并且只会保留 30 天的历史记录。管理员还可以阻止关注者截取屏幕截图或转发消息。频道不是端到端加密的，但 WhatsApp 表示正在为非营利组织、健康组织或其他对隐私敏感的组织探索这个想法。 </p><div id="427c965c6f5641c4845815499f2e9e29"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Fwk7bPOUHM4?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen="" scrolling="no"></iframe></div><p> Channels 或多或少是<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/telegram-channel-ads-192249765.html">竞争对手同名聊天应用 Telegram</a>上类似功能的副本。今年早些时候，Meta 在 Instagram 上<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-is-bringing-telegram-like-channels-to-instagram-184054107.html?guccounter=1">推出了</a>广播频道，让创作者可以像 WhatsApp 用户一样将<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://about.fb.com/news/2023/02/instagram-broadcast-channels-creators-deepen-connections-with-followers/">更新流式</a>传输到他们的粉丝的收件箱中。该功能可以比作时事通讯，事实上，它<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.androidpolice.com/whatsapp-channels-rumored-newsletter-tool/">可能在开发时就被称为</a>时事通讯（或者后者可能会在以后作为单独的功能出现）。</p><p> WhatsApp 的发展已经远远超出了它作为一个简单的消息应用程序的初衷。 Meta 最近增加了<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/whatsapp-now-lets-you-use-your-account-on-multiple-phones-163158921.html">在多个设备上使用一个帐户的</a>功能，这在以前不仅是不可能的，而且在您更换手机时可能会造成麻烦。该公司还更新了群聊，同时增加了投票、购物等功能。</p><p>该公司表示，新功能并未广泛推出，而是从“领先的全球组织和哥伦比亚和新加坡的精选组织”开始。它将在“未来几个月”到达更多国家和用户。</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/whatsapps-new-channels-feature-lets-accounts-send-one-way-updates-to-followers-090843232.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/whatsapps-new-channels-feature-lets-accounts-send-one-way-updates-to-followers-090843232.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> fe7cc50f-3d24-4602-a469-8c37525d1e62</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Thu, 08 Jun 2023 09:08:43 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1686226846</ingested><modified> 2023-06-08T12:20:50+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="1107" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/c0730080-05f6-11ee-aae9-7298848385ab" width="1868"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1107" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/c0730080-05f6-11ee-aae9-7298848385ab" width="1868"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[WhatsApp]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Three mockups of WhatsApp screens display the new WhatsApp Channels feature for private one-way broadcasts to followers.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[WhatsApp]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[FCC orders Avid Telecom to stop health insurance-related robocalls]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>联邦通信委员会已向 Avid Telecom <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.fcc.gov/document/fcc-looks-cut-insurance-related-robocall-campaign">发出</a>停止和终止信函，Avid Telecom 是同一家公司，几乎所有美国总检察长都以<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/company-responsible-for-75-billion-robocalls-sued-by-nearly-every-attorney-general-220050450.html">涉嫌抢劫电话活动</a>为由起诉了这家公司。在致 Avid 首席执行官迈克尔兰斯基<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://docs.fcc.gov/public/attachments/DOC-394134A1.pdf">的信</a>(PDF) 中，FCC 表示已确定该公司“显然代表其一个或多个客户发起非法机器人电话流量。”该委员会解释说，它与 USTelecom 的 Industry Traceback Group 合作，调查了与健康保险相关的预先录制的电话营销电话，上述州检察长将这些电话确认为未经同意的机器人电话。</p><p>显然，他们的调查确定 Avid 发起了这些电话。当接到电话通知时，Avid 告诉追溯小组，其客户通过选择加入的网站获得了同意，但 FCC 在信中解释说，客户“未能充分披露以获得同意”。也就是说，它没有告诉人们他们的同意授权呼叫者“使用自动拨号器或人工或预先录制的声音来传递广告或电话营销信息”。在某些情况下，据称客户甚至在他们撤销同意后仍打电话给他们。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> FCC 概述了 Avid 必须采取的解决问题的步骤，首先是调查已识别的流量。然后，它必须采取措施防止新客户和现有客户使用其网络拨打非法电话。在收到这封信后的 48 小时内，Avid 必须向 FCC 更新其为减少来自其网络的机器人电话而采取的措施。之后，它必须向委员会通报其已实施的保护措施，以防止其客户使用其网络拨打机器人电话。 FCC 警告说，如果 Avid 不遵守规定，下游语音服务提供商可能会永久阻止 Avid 的所有流量。</p><p> 5 月下旬，来自 48 个州的总检察长对总部位于亚利桑那州的 VoIP 服务提供商提起诉讼，指控它是向国家谢绝来电登记处的人们拨打超过 75 亿通电话的来源。根据诉讼，Avid 伪造了电话号码，让电话看起来像是来自政府办公室、执法机构和亚马逊等公司。总检察长要求法院对 Avid 发出禁止拨打机器人电话的禁令，并要求该公司支付损害赔偿金并向其非法呼叫的人进行赔偿。</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/fcc-orders-avid-telecom-to-stop-health-insurance-related-robocalls-064428940.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/fcc-orders-avid-telecom-to-stop-health-insurance-related-robocalls-064428940.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 59cb90e8-d82b-447b-8b2f-c85159eaec0c</guid><dc:creator>玛丽拉月亮</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Thu, 08 Jun 2023 06:44:28 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1686206670</ingested><modified> 2023-06-08T06:44:35+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Company Legal & Law Matters]]></category><category><![CDATA[Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="4160" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/eafde980-05c1-11ee-9bff-e02e3f03a4cc" width="6240"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="4160" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/eafde980-05c1-11ee-9bff-e02e3f03a4cc" width="6240"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Thai Liang Lim via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A woman receiving an incoming suspected spam call on her phone. The network provider detect the scam and show warning sign, woman rejects the call.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Person receiving suspected spam call on smartphone from an unknown caller]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Reddit says some accessibility apps won’t have to pay for its API]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Reddit 正在为一些专注于可访问性的应用程序的制造商更改其有争议的新 API 政策，前提是他们不通过其服务获利。作为<em>边缘</em><ins><a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/6/7/23752804/reddit-exempt-accessibility-apps-api-pricing-changes">报告，</a></ins> Reddit 已决定为强调可访问性功能的精选“非商业”应用程序的开发人员提供豁免，使其免受其有争议的新定价结构的影响。</p><p> Reddit 发言人蒂姆·拉斯施密特 (Tim Rathschmidt) 在一份声明中表示：“我们已经与一些非商业应用程序的开发商联系，以满足可访问性需求，并向他们提供我们大规模定价条款的豁免。” He declined to name any specific services or share how many apps might be covered by the new exemption, citing ongoing conversations with developers.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> The concession comes amid growing anger with Reddit over the planned changes, which many developers say will put them out of business. Last week, Christian Selig, the developer of Apollo, said the new pricing would cost him<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/reddit-app-developer-says-the-sites-new-api-rules-will-cost-him-20-million-a-year-203911487.html">$20 million</a></ins> a year to keep the app running in its current state. Other developers have voiced similar concerns about the changes, currently slated to take effect July 1st.</p><p> As <em>The Verge</em> points out, the API changes have also sparked widespread concern among Reddit users who depend on services that make it easier to use the site with screen readers and other accessibility aids. Earlier this week, the moderators of r/Blind said they were planning to join the upcoming<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/reddit-communities-are-going-dark-to-protest-changes-that-would-hurt-third-party-apps-154133342.html">Reddit blackout</a></ins> in protest of the changes. The effort, which more than 1,000 subreddits have signed onto, will see<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.reddit.com/r/ModCoord/comments/1401qw5/incomplete_and_growing_list_of_participating/">participating</a></ins><ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.reddit.com/r/ModCoord/comments/143fzf6/incomplete_and_growing_list_of_participating/?utm_source=reddit&amp;utm_medium=usertext&amp;utm_name=ModCoord&amp;utm_content=t3_1401qw5">communities</a></ins> “go dark” for 48 hours.</p><p> While the latest change from Reddit could bring some relief to the members of r/Blind and others who depend on apps specifically tailored to their needs, the rule change won&#39;t help the majority of third-party app developers. Apps like Apollo, RIF and BaconReader are monetized and thus don&#39;t qualify for an exemption even though some also offer robust accessibility features. Unless Reddit makes further concessions, those developers are still facing the possibility that they will be forced to shut down, or drastically alter, their services.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/reddit-says-some-accessibility-apps-wont-have-to-pay-for-its-api-213401412.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/reddit-says-some-accessibility-apps-wont-have-to-pay-for-its-api-213401412.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> ab89c0fa-6974-4e2c-880d-985842df9798</guid><dc:creator> Karissa Bell</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Wed, 07 Jun 2023 21:34:01 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1686173642</ingested><modified> 2023-06-07T21:34:06+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Software]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Karissa Bell]]></category><media:content height="2200" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/cd746af0-0577-11ee-bff9-5c4f89998d61" width="3300"><media:keywords> headline </media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2200" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/cd746af0-0577-11ee-bff9-5c4f89998d61" width="3300"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[SOPA Images via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[POLAND - 2023/01/06: In this photo illustration a Reddit logo seen displayed on a smartphone. (Photo Illustration by Mateusz Slodkowski/SOPA Images/LightRocket via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[In this photo illustration a Reddit logo seen displayed on a...]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best tablets for 2023]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Following the release of the <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-ipad-air-5th-generation-review-130019050.html">2022 Apple iPad Air</a> and Samsung&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-tab-s-8-review-in-a-class-of-its-own-132946024.html">Galaxy Tab S8 line</a> last year, there hasn&#39;t been a ton of movement in the tablet world. At IFA, Lenovo announced refreshed versions of the <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/lenovo-ideapad-5-i-chromebook-announced-specs-availability-pricing-040045300.html">Tab P11 and P11 Pro</a> featuring updated internals and even an 11.2-inch OLED display with a 120Hz refresh rate on the Pro. Apple&#39;s latest tablet is the revamped 10.9-inch iPad, but at $449, it&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-ipads-how-to-pick-the-best-apple-tablet-for-you-150054066.html">more of an upgrade from</a> , rather than alternative for, the less expensive 10.2-inch iPad. More recently, Amazon launched revamped versions of its <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-fire-hd-8-plus-kids-tablet-2022-price-release-date-130025038.html">Fire HD 8 tablets</a> featuring new “Tap to Alexa” functionality. While there haven&#39;t been a ton of groundbreaking releases as of late, you still have a bunch of great tablets to choose from if you&#39;re in the market for a new one or are looking for a laptop replacement. Let&#39;s break down what you should consider before deciding on a new device, and our current top picks for the best tablets.</p><h2><br> Which OS is right for me?</h2><p> Before you even start looking at specific devices, consider how your new tablet will fit in with the gadgets you already own, and how you plan to use it. For example, if everyone in your house uses Macs and iPhones, it probably doesn&#39;t make a lot of sense to buy an Android tablet, even if you&#39;ve been tempted by the massive 14.6-inch screen on the new <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-galaxy-tab-s8-ultra-hands-on-price-specs-features-150056575.html">Galaxy Tab S8 Ultra.</a> This goes double for anyone with an extensive library of purchased videos and music that might be harder to access after switching platforms.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Another consideration is the kind of work you&#39;ll be doing. That&#39;s because while most modern tablets are adept at browsing websites or playing games, some operating systems like iPadOS and Windows 11 are better designed to support multitasking and productivity than Android or even Chrome OS. It&#39;s a similar situation for software, because while most popular apps and games are available on both Apple&#39;s App Store and Google&#39;s Play Store, more specialized software may only have proper support on desktop platforms like Windows or macOS.</p><h2> What size screen should I get?</h2><p> Figuring out the best screen size for you will also be related to the kind of work (or play) you intend to do. Larger displays make it much easier to view two apps side by side, and big screens also deliver a more immersive movie viewing experience. But at the same time, the larger the tablet, the less likely you&#39;re going to want to move it around. That means you&#39;re not only going to want to take stock of your workspace (ie, if you have a desk or instead plan to work from a couch or even your bed), you&#39;re also going to want to think about how the device will fit into your everyday routine or commute (if you have one).</p><h2> Potential accessories</h2><p> Finally, you&#39;ll want to consider any add-ons or accessories you&#39;re planning to use, which can range from detachable keyboards to things like external mics or a stylus. The good news is that many of the best tablets nowadays offer some kind of keyboard accessory, which allows the device to function more like a 2-in-1 instead of simply being a content consumption device. Some tablets also feature things like microSD card slots that support expandable storage, or optional 4G or 5G connectivity, which can be a real boon to frequent travelers. And if you&#39;re planning to use the tablet mainly for work, you might want to grab a USB hub for connecting all your favorite peripherals.</p><h2> Best overall: Apple iPad Pro</h2><p><core-commerce id="ee244226ac8f41a6a6963b8dee9b2ab6" data-type="product-list"></p><p> Powered by the same Apple M2 chips you get in MacBooks, the <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9zdG9yZXMvcGFnZS80NUUxNDM0QS1GRDU4LTQwQTctQkMxNC1BNjk4Q0QzNkRGN0M_&amp;signature=AQAAAZtPDfg5pd1RjnTecI9phynDaRaaLjiKYx-zC0Bi7XBO&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fstores%2Fpage%2F45E1434A-FD58-40A7-BC14-A698CD36DF7C%3F_encoding%3DUTF8%26store_ref%3DSB_A08778292RIRQ4ZUH855M%26pd_rd_plhdr%3Dt%26aaxitk%3D094f12dbd533746035ea73fa272aab9f%26hsa_cr_id%3D4219929570501%26lp_asins%3DB09323PCV7%2CB09QHXTHYZ%26lp_query%3Dipad%2Bpro%26lp_slot%3Dauto-sparkle-hsa-tetris%26pd_rd_w%3D3YSC5%26pf_rd_p%3D488a18be-6d86-4de0-8607-bd4ea4b560f3%26pd_rd_wg%3DwZIHz%26pf_rd_r%3DJC6ZAVKVCP3XWFPMPVQA%26pd_rd_r%3D831f2cf4-13f7-48da-869d-440099b8f100%26">iPad Pro</a> is the best iPad and one of the most well-built tablets you can buy today. It&#39;s available in <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-ipad-pro-2021-m1-review-liquid-retina-xdr-5g-features-price-130049005.html">two sizes</a> (11 and 12.9 inches) and works with a range of accessories including the <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAQM2L5ruY23Krn3s2MmnmYL8u37RxJgD8pauGA_NzKoT&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FApple-MU8F2AM-A-Pencil-Generation%2Fdp%2FB07K1WWBJK">Apple Pencil</a> and the extremely useful (but pricey) <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAfOWeDl4x8J2EiBAT7Jt9cqgbcb4KnrS1Q-lCqXXxzJY&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FMagic-Keyboard-11-inch-iPad-Generation%2Fdp%2FB0863BQJMS">Magic Keyboard</a> . And thanks to their 120Hz ProMotion mini-LED displays, the iPad Pro&#39;s screen boasts strong brightness and fluid visuals, regardless of whether you&#39;re watching a movie or creating a slideshow presentation. Recent versions of iPadOS have also made Apple&#39;s most premium tablet a much more capable work device, with the addition of new sidebars for quickly switching between apps, a more powerful desktop-like UI for Safari, and various new toolbars throughout.</p><p> The main downside is that starting at <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9BcHBsZS0xMS1pbmNoLWlQYWQtUHJvLVdpLUZpLTEyOEdCL2RwL0IwQkpMQktNVjg_d